    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-05-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-05-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="560"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d560">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Sir <persName
                            type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-05-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 13, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 101.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to state that the
                    revenue-cutter <hi rend="italic">Perry</hi> intends to sail from San Francisco
                    for Bering Sea on to-morrow; the 14th instant, and to inquire whether you have
                    received the names of the British vessels, with their officers, spoken of in my
                    note of the 7th instant. In case you have not yet received the desired
                    information, I shall very greatly appreciate your courtesy in telegraphing for
                    it, so that this Government may be apprised thereof to-day or at the earliest
                    possible moment.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
